      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TERILEE (3) looks the one to beat again. She won very smartly last start at Sandown Hillside over 1400m, coming away late to score by 1.75 lengths. She's off a let up here but the stable keep them fit and she's always promised to get over a bit of ground so the mile should suit. CHIRINGITA (5) presents third up here having been good in two runs back. She'll be fitter again and can improve. AUTUMN SLIDE (6) ran well first up at Cranbourne when getting home late in a bunched finish. She should be much better suited up to this trip and has claims. A DIVA (4) won well fresh at Cranbourne as a $3 hope to build on her imposing record. She has upside and can go on with it.",
